rComments: Horrible Prof. Explains okay in class, but Quizzes are un predictable. Marks hard and is very tough to argue with.

He was quite good explaining at explaining things in lecture, but his tests were quite difficult. His tests focus more on memorization rather on whether or not you actually learned anything. EVERYTHING is testable.

Prof is very good at explaining things in lectures and the test/exam was easy...just memorize all the lectures. BUT the essays were marked EXTREMELY hard and ppl that always write essays for other courses get bad essay marks in this course! No essay guideline/helpful comments so you don't know how to fix it. The info learned in class is pretty cool
Hes really good, one of the best prof at utm
What I found weird about him is that he gets ticked off at the stupidest things and gets very rude. Course load is light, but all material you do cover is all testable, and has to be known very well.
